sub_title: Chief Scientific Officer & Co-founder at Clear.bio
summary:
Madelon Bracke is co-founder and CSO at Clear. She is an allround life sciences and health professional, with experience in research, education and entrepreneurship. She started her career in biology, obtained a PhD in cell biology, and worked as scientist in the fields of immunology, hematology, pharmacoepidemiology, regenerative medicine & stem cells, in the Netherlands and the UK. She authored many scientific publications, supervised PhD students, acquired grants and was principle investigator on strategic alliances between industry and academia. 
After 15 years in academia, she moved to biotech and headed an R&D bioreactor technology platform were she was involved in product development, strategic planning and business development, certification, coordination and participation in (inter)national researchconsortia. She is inventor on several patents. 
Triggered by start-up challenges, she directed her professional steps towards entrepreneurship and innovation. During a sabbatical year in Boston, she took on freelance consultancy projects and knowledge and experience in entrepreneurship, organizational analysis and business strategy. 
In the last ten years, she focused on valorisation of research in education and entrepreneurship. She has been an executive and consultant for several start-up. She held different positions at the UMC Utrecht, including program manager of the Global Executive Masters of Business Innovation and Entrepreneurship in Life Sciences & Health and program manager of the UMCU Educational Strategy Fit for the Future. As an expert and coach she regularly advises start-ups in the life sciences and health business.
